1.title: Pilot
1.plot: Minda is a woman who, in her desperation to be with someone, easily falls for Daniel. An account of heartache and betrayal, witness how the man Minda loves instantly turns into her worst nightmare once her gay son Ryan enters the picture.

2.title: Losyang
2.plot: It was a perfect marriage for Tere and Marlon until a woman from her husband's workplace intervened.

3.title: Instant Baby
3.plot: Husband and wife Paul and Lily cannot bear a child so when Rowena agreed to adopt her yet-to-be-born baby, it is like a gift from heaven.

4.title: Mama's Boy
4.plot: Former night club dancer Abby married Marcus in the hopes of finding a better life. But her new husband's extreme attachment to his own mother threatens to their wreck their starting marriage.

5.title: Postpartum Depression
5.plot: After giving birth, Joan suffered from postpartum depression, causing her to become a troublemaker, a nuisance to her husband and immediate community.

6.title: Sugar Daddy
6.plot: Girlie went to Japan as an entertainer against her husband's will to provide for the family. After three years, she reveals that she has a sugar daddy, and she's coming home with him.

7.title: Scandal
7.plot: Marose's dream of getting married is compromised because of an ex-boyfriend threatening to leak their sex scandal to the public.

8.title: Kasambahay
8.plot: Ces has forgiven her husband's unfaithful conquests in the past and is trying to keep their marriage from falling apart. However, things go wrong as soon as the new house maid arrives.

9.title: Kambal
9.plot: Conjoined twins AJ and TJ are not just brothers, they're also partners in crime. But when the twins meet Rachel, all hell breaks loose as the two become bitter rivals for her affection.

10.title: Mrs. Husband
10.plot: Anton is a college professor who's married to a loving wife and a father to their two boys. But on his 50th birthday, he decides to surprise everyone by coming out of the closet.

11.title: Karma
11.plot: Monique is about to make the biggest mistake of her life. She's about to marry Jericho, a professional swindler.

12.title: Martir
12.plot: Emily blindly believes that her relationship with Alvin can work in spite of his drug addiction.

13.title: Batang ina
13.plot: Mela and Lorenz are high school sweethearts. But things started to turn sour when Mela got pregnant, provoking the ire of Lorenz' mother.

14.title: Tres rosas
14.plot: Maring's past as a comfort woman still haunts her, and the nightmare came back to life when her grand daughter Rose comes home with a Japanese fiancé.

15.title: Talent
15.plot: Aspiring actor Adrian sought Warren's service as a talent manager. But Warren will ask for a fee that does not involve money, but his heart.

16.title: CCTV
16.plot: Robert (Fabio Ide) develops a weird fetish for sharing his wife Anne (Solenn Heussaff) to their driver (Mark Herras) after an accident left him invalid from the waist down.

17.title: Sir
17.plot: Minnie develops deep feelings for her teacher Pat and tries to sway him to like her too.

18.title: Bayaw
18.plot: Belen feels repressed and neglected as a housewife and finds herself drawn to the arms of her husband's brother.

19.title: Cougar
19.plot: Lara's (Diana Zubiri) bond with her best friend Sandra (Katya Santos) is put to test when she decides to have an intimate relationship with Sandra's son (Hiro Peralta).

20.title: Coma
20.plot: Ricky (Rodjun Cruz) suffers from amnesia and lost his memories of Lara (Max Collins), his fiancé. Lara works to win him back but Ricky already married another woman, his doctor.

21.title: Unhappy Wife
21.plot: Will a husband's (Carlos Agassi) inability to fulfill his wife's (Jackie Rice) longing for physical contact lead her to infidelity?

22.title: Laro
22.plot: What seems to be a trivial mischief for a call center team leader eventually leads to a devastating series of events.

23.title: Tuhog
23.plot: Melissa (LJ Reyes) entrusted her family to her sister Linda (Ryza Cenon) so she could work in the city and provide for their needs. But when she returns, she finds out Linda has gotten more than close to her husband (Pancho Magno).

24.title: Baliw
24.plot: What would you if the man you love turns out to be psychotic? Would you save his sanity or save your self first?

25.title: Sulot
25.plot: Jane (Jade Lopez) and gay Mico (Gio Alvarez) are best of friends. But when Mico arrives with a new lover (Kiko Matos), Jane can't help but feel attraction for her best friend's man.

26.title: Utol
26.plot: Julius (Kiko Estrada) and Jane (Kim Rodriguez) are siblings with a dark secret. And with the arrival of their mom's new lover (Arthur Solinap), their scandalous affair threatens to leak.

27.title: Sumpa
27.plot: A mermaid lures a fisherman to his death to avenge the ocean's degradation because of dynamite fishing.

28.title: Gayuma
28.plot: Diego is head over heels in love with Clarissa who already made it clear that she can never return his affections. Diego turns to black magic to win her instead.

29.title: Pamana
29.plot: In a remote town, locals believe that Myra is an "aswang." Unaware of her reputation, Paolo woos the mysterious woman to his arms.

30.title: Balo
30.plot: Caring brings home her husband's corpse after learning his body did not decay after years underground.

31.title: Webcam
31.plot: With the desire to recover his child from kidnappers, Michael is forced to enter an illegal online prostitution.

32.title: Face Value
32.plot: Because Divine is unattractive than her handsome boyfriend, their photos in social media are insulted and taunted.

33.title: Stepfather
33.plot: Carmen meets Jess in a KTV bar. They formed an instant bond which led to love, and so they decided to live together. Because of their love, Carmen had high hopes that Jess will treat Kat-kat, her daughter, like his own. Jess did everything to win Kat-kat's approval which led to the unthinkable - a sin that might change their lives forever.

34.title: Apartment
34.plot: AJ, Pherry and James decide to rent a secret apartment. The apartment serves as a lover's den for them and their secret girlfriends. These three boys have a tendency to rely on cougars such as Donna and Sally , who are longing for the love and sweetness of their respective husbands. AJ's life changes when he meets Alex, a pretty lady whose age is the same as his, and lives in the same apartment building. AJ and Alex's meeting will start a chain of events that lead to the revelation of the three boys' secrets, even Alex's own.

35.title: Status Symbol
35.plot: For many women, their bag is not just about for carrying things but it is a form of expression, a part of their identity and a status symbol.

36.title: Blackmail
36.plot: Mika did not expect that a fellow countryman would take advantage of her and extort blackmail from her.

37.title: Piano
37.plot: Because of Miranda's (Elizabeth Oropesa) extreme loneliness, she didn't notice that she already fell in love with her much younger helper Ato (Derrick Monasterio).

38.title: Daddy Santa
38.plot:

49.title: Old Maid
49.plot: All her life Zeny (Ces Quesada) worked for the family of Abel (Tommy Abuel). When his wife died she decided to stay to take care of Abel. Things turned ugly when Abel's prodigal son Jacob (Marco Alcaraz) returned to live with them together with his pregnant girlfriend Chloe (Yasmien Kurdi)

50.title: Wanted: Tatay
50.plot: Eva (Valerie Concepcion) is a broken-hearted girl from the province. She travels to the metro to start a new life. There, she befriends city boys Emir (Luis Alandy), Kulet (Archie Alemania), and Patel (JC Santos) not knowing that they will bring her harm than good.

51.title: Inay
51.plot: Emilia (Angel Aquino) dedicated her life to her mom Adela (Anita Linda). But when she fell in love with David (Benjamin Alves), Adela came between them. She feared her daughter will settle down with David and ultimately leave her. Who will Emilia choose, her mom or the love of her life?

52.title: Unico Hijo
52.plot: Lina (Cherry Pie Picache) believes her sole mission in life is to give his only son, Miguel (Martin del Rosario), a bright future. When her "perfect" son revealed a dark secret, her world turns upside down.

53.title: Fake Wife
53.plot: Michelle (Kris Bernal) marries a foreign investor named Frank (Fabio Ide) for convenience and business purposes. Will this fake marriage eventually blossom into a fairy tale love story or a nightmare in the making?

54.title: Insecure Wife
54.plot: Maita (Roxanne Barcelo) has always been attracted to married men. When she met Jun (Gardo Versoza), the husband of her landlady (Francine Prieto), there's no turning back in seducing her next victim.

55.title: Live In
55.plot: Dennis (Tom Rodriguez) and Miriam (Carla Abellana) are live-in partners for 7 years. However, the passion seems to be fading. Is marriage an option to save their relationship?

56.title: Hiya
56.plot: Gail (Bea Binene) is a simple girl who thrives in her studies as a scholar. But all the simplicity she portrays will change once she met the gorgeous hunk and school heartthrob named EJ (Derrick Monasterio).

57.title: Two Mothers
57.plot: Olive (Ana Capri) is a dedicated and caring stepmom to Jonas (Sean Ross), the son of the her current beau Gary (Jay Manalo). But when the real mom of Jonas, Liza (Precious Lara Quigaman), came back after being away for years, things suddenly became complicated for the whole family.

58.title: Pagsubok
58.plot: Ben (Bobby Andrews) is a dedicated sales agent who's never really successful in his work while his wife, (Angelu de Leon), who works in the same company, has already stepped up the corporate ladder. What will happen in a marriage when the husband is insecure with his own wife?

59.title: Ex
59.plot: Melissa (Gwen Zamora) is pregnant with Nestor's child (Carlos Agassi), and their relationship has gone sour because of the former's pregnancy mood swings. One drunken night, Nestor and his former wife Joan (Jade Lopez) got into a sneaky sexy time during a company party. It turns out Nestor and Joan are still officially husband and wife because their marriage has not yet been annulled. Is Nestor committing adultery? What will happen to Melissa?

60.title: Mama Beth
60.plot: Mama Beth (Gina Alajar) is the loving mother of Ana (Thea Tolentino). But when the latter decided to work overseas, her mother assumed the task of taking care of the family she left, her child Myka and her husband Neil (Kristoffer Martin). The simple life assumed by Mama Beth turned into nightmare when Neil showed his true colors.

61.title: Tatay-tatayan
61.plot: Elvin (Alex Medina) and Norman (Arnold Reyes) are proud parents to their son James (David Remo). Their sweet and happy home is suddenly threatened when the real mother of James arrive.

62.title: Asset
62.plot: Claire (LJ Reyes) is one of the best intelligence assets of the police force. Jerry (Ryan Eigenmann), a dedicated policeman, started a romance with Claire that will eventually become abusive.

63.title: Sabong
63.plot: Allan (TJ Trinidad) is cockfight gambler; and just like his hobby, his married life is a gamble as he juggles his attention and love to his two wives, Rheena (Aubrey Miles) and Lorraine (Ara Mina), who happen to agree on staying under the same roof.

64.title: Bisita
64.plot: Harvey (Archie Alemania) and Katie (Karen delos Reyes) are in the middle of planning their wedding when a mysterious woman (Sheree Bautista) arrives.

65.title: Kulam
65.plot: Daniel (Mike Tan) works in a piggery business and didn't have much time with his wife Marita (Valeen Montenegro) who has been longing for them to finally have a child. Unknown to Marita, her husband is actually very much preoccupied with another dirty business.

66.title: Raketera
66.plot: Anton (Joross Gamboa) tries to save her girlfriend Cristina (Jackie Rice), who is secretly working in a massage parlor known for its additional treatment.

67.title: Reyna
67.plot: Because of his uncontrolled feelings for Liz (Kim Rodriguez), Dondon (Kiko Matos) came to a point that he felt a strong desire to kill her.

68.title: Dahas
68.plot: Rosita (Joyce Ching) was raped by her older brother Olan (Martin Del Rosario) which later on led to pregnancy.

69.title: Tenant
69.plot: Greg (Pen Medina) falls in love with Tina (Aubrey Miles), her new border, and soon will discover her dirty secrets.

1.title: Ex ni BFF
1.plot: Girl code of two best friends was broken because of a young boy.

2.title: Misyonero
2.plot: Jerry and Sherwin were sent to an isolated town to teach the children how to read and write. With their dedication to their service, the twins will eventually win the hearts of the residents of the barrio governed by Tasoy, including that of Baning, who would do anything for Jerry to fall in love with her and have him bring her to Manila. But Abel will not let this happen as he has been in love with Baning for a long time now.

3.title: Gold Digger
3.plot: Sheila (Winwyn Marquez) dreams of finding the man of her dreams that will eventually help her and her family to alleviate poverty. Luckily, she met Nick (Mark McMahon), a good looking and wealthy foreigner who is willing to help them improve their lives. But what if Sheila's family only sees Nick for the money and not the man who truly loves her? What will happen to their love story?

4.title: Boy Hipon
4.plot: Edwin (JC Tiuseco) is a veteran of male beauty pageants because of his perfect body. But his body is not only for beauty pageants, he also uses this to attract and deceive women.

5.title: Trip
5.plot: Luke (Troy Montero) is a yoga instructor who Zoey (Katrina Halili) fantasizes about. With the help of her best friend Berry (Jade Lopez) and call girl Mimi (Francine Prieto), she will unveil the real meaning of her fantasies and why she is so drawn to this mysterious yoga instructor.

6.title: Madam Z
6.plot: A man-hater accidentally falls in love with her employee who has a wife and child.

7.title: Transwoman
7.plot: Queen (Trixie Maristela) is an attractive transwoman. She may have the look of a perfect woman but love seems just an elusive dream for her. This will change when she meets Glen (James Blanco), the married bartender in the bar where she is working.

8.title: Rigodon
8.plot: Ian (Martin del Rosario), Michael (Sebastian Castro), April (Roxanne Barcelo) and Kris (Stephanie Sol) are tenants of an apartment that will become witness to their intertwined relationships.

9.title: Poser
9.plot: Marvin (Ruru Madrid) is a smart, shy student who wants to be part of the swimming team. But when bullying inside the swim team turned dark and horrifying, Marvin sought revenge.

10.title: Nanay prosti
10.plot: Due to an unexpected tragedy, Doray (Nova Villa) accepts Luding's (Chanda Romero) offer to become a prostitute at night so she can buy Tomas' (Roi Vinzon) medicines.
